{
  "texts": [
    "Their study thus highlights the promising capabilities of deep learning in noise reduction scenarios.",
    "Quan et al. (2020) presented a non-blind image deblurring technique employing complex-valued CNN (CV-CNN).",
    "The uniqueness of their approach lies in incorporating Gabor-domain denoising as a prior step in the deconvolution model.",
    "By evaluating their model using quantitative metrics like Peak Signal-to-Noise Ratio (PSNR) and Structural Similarity Index (SSIM), their work showcased effective deblurring outcomes, reaffirming the potential of complex-valued CNNs in image restoration.",
    "Jin et al. (2021) harnessed the power of deep learning, specifically the pix2pixHD model, to enhance multidetector computed tomography (MDCT) images."
  ]
}